              <h2>How this long-term capital gains tax calculator works</h2>
              <p>
                This calculator estimates your U.S. federal long-term capital
                gains tax using the standard 0%, 15%, and 20% brackets. It
                follows the IRS ordering rules in a simplified way:
              </p>
              <ol>
                <li>
                  Start with your ordinary taxable income (wages, interest,
                  short-term gains, etc.).
                </li>
                <li>
                  Net your long-term gains with long-term losses and any
                  long-term loss carryover.
                </li>
                <li>
                  Optionally net short-term gains and losses and apply up to
                  $3,000 of net capital loss against ordinary income.
                </li>
                <li>
                  Add your net long-term gain on top of ordinary income and
                  apply the long-term capital gains brackets for your filing
                  status.
                </li>
              </ol>

              <h3>Long-term capital gains tax brackets (2024)</h3>
              <p>
                The table below shows the 2024 federal long-term capital gains
                brackets for most assets:
              </p>

              <div class="overflow-x-auto">
                <table class="min-w-full text-sm border border-gray-200">
                  <thead class="bg-gray-100">
                    <tr>
                      <th class="px-3 py-2 text-left border-b">
